CatDescriptText: Jake Milliones was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Out series published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 27, 1973, pg. 4 with question: "Pittsburghers were asked if they felt our city would ever have a Black mayor, and if so, who they thought the person would be." Answer reads: "I don't believe we will have a Black mayor here any time soon. I'm sure there's somebody around, but am not certain who that is.  I believe Mayor Jackson will have a large job on his hands in Atlanta."
